There are a few different ways to think about how to find side QR. One way is to use trigonometry: $\tan(30)=QR/9\sqrt{3}$. Since $\tan(30)=1/\sqrt{3}$, we can see that QR is an integer: [tex]
&\tan(30)=\dfrac{\overline{QR}}{\overline{PR}} \\ 
&\tan(30)=\dfrac{\overline{QR}}{9\sqrt{3}} \\ 
&\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{3}}=\dfrac{\overline{QR}}{9\sqrt{3}} \\ 
&\sqrt{3}\cdot\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{3}} = \dfrac{\overline{QR}}{\cancel{\sqrt{3}}}\cdot \cancel{\sqrt{3}} \\ 
&1 = \overline{QR}
[/tex] 

